{"questionId":"26455","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the equation of the normal to the curve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;in the form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>finding gradient at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><menclose notation=\"right\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></menclose><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>finding the perpendicular gradient&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mo>⊥</mo></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong> </em>for correctly substituting&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;and their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mo>⊥</mo></msub></math>.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award the final <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>if the answer is not in the required form. Accept integer multiples of the equation.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26455","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.9b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the equation of the normal to the curve y=fx at 1, 2 in the form ax+by+d=0, where a, b, d∈ℤ.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.4—Tangents and normal"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}